{
  "number": 3065,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3065",
  "title": "Star widget renders even when it shouldn't",
  "body": "**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\nCome to our attention that when rendering a star widget; if there are no facet values associated, the widget still shows whereas all other facet widgets do not render.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce 🔍**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Create a facet for rating\r\n2. Create a set of records where none of them have the facet value for rating\r\n3. Create a star widget in instantsearch.js\r\n4. Observe that the widget is visible even though there should be no associated facet values with the given search.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior 💭**\r\nThe widget should hide itself",
